def: Placed in a niche. "Those niched shapes of noble mold."Tennyson.
A gull in the plumage of its first year.

Said of crystalline rocks which contain a relatively lowpercentage of silica, as basalt. Basic salt (Chem.), a salt formedfrom a base or hydroxide by the partial replacement of its hydrogenby a negative or acid element or radical.
An iron needle for piercing the cartridge of a cannon beforepriming.
A mineral of an olive-green color, commonly in orthorhombiccrystals. It is a hydrous phosphate of copper.
To pull away. [Obs.]Yet are not these parts avelled. Sir T. Browne.
To commit adultery; to pollute. [Obs.] B. Jonson.
